cs.DM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SI 

The paper deals with algorithms for recovering planted solutions in two well-known models, the stochastic block model and planted constraint satisfaction problems, which are both related to topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The algorithm also involves subsampling and keeping track of multiple norms, which are techniques commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
